      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "For comparison, a naive model that predicts spectra based on the proportion of bitter and nonbitter spectra in the training set was used... Prediction was performed for compounds extracted from external test set 1 and external test set 2 (Table 4)... The results were then combined, and the final label was selected based on the majority of the predictions.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper demonstrates organizing predictions into structured outputs (Table 4 shows predictions mapped to compounds with precision/recall metrics), but the paper focuses on BitterMasS (mass spectrum-based) predictions, not BitterPredict (structure-based) predictions. The scope describes a BitterPredict workflow, but the paper's primary contribution is BitterMasS. The general workflow of compiling predictions into structured format is supported, but the specific tool focus (BitterPredict.m) is not the paper's main subject.",
